content:
@Lynx, <a class="postlink post_tag" href="https://forum.mafiascum.net/viewtopic.php?p=6319950#p6319950">93</a>: Everyone is obvious town to themselves, unless they are obvious scum to themselves. That I am addressing another one of your weird comprehension issues is distressing, Lynx.<br>
<br>
The point of that post was why I was then not interested in hearing serrapaladin's reasonings, as it could not be very different from what I had posted.

@Indigo Heron: Why the lack of voting? For what are you waiting?<br>
@evilpacman18: ^<br>
@chaoslord54: ^

@ Beck - I thought I was baiting scum, but you're better at turning the tables than I am, I suppose. I just might like you a little. And my vote on Madonna was purely RVS. That post referred to a vote with intent to lynch (I'm pretty sure there's a difference.) And I really enjoyed AHS, Season 1, by the way. I highly suggest it to anyone.<br>
<br>
@bruin - Are you sure? I keep getting called scum in all my games. I just want to be myself, but its not working out for me. *shrug*

@madonna, tbh none of those are good reasons for Sera. Omgus is null, trying to start a wagon on you is actually kind of protown if you think about it. He's trying to get the game out of RVs and start wagoning somebody. Sure that somebody just happed to be you, so I understand why you take offense to him, but it really doesn't look scummy to me. <br>
<br>
I agree we need to focus, so i suggest you join me on lynx.

Toshibite strikes me as really misguided. His self-vote was dumb, he refused to acknowledge it, and then his vote goes to Lynx with the little note of "if I die, lynch Lynx" as if that was all the martyr-detective work we need around here. He talked of not wanting to be biased while he self-voted, OMGUSed Lynx, but notably called out bruin because the Bruins suck or something? Aaaaaand, you know what, beyond that, he has not really done much as I thought since that time, so he should be further down that read list, much lower.<br>
<br>
Hmm, I think I have wall of texted enough. Yes, I will stop there. ^_^;;

@bruin: The question was "Why did you not vote?", not "Why did you not vote Aronis?".<br>
<br>
@Belisarius: Glad to see you back attacking inactives. Aronis was too pressing yesterday to keep to that mantra you had? No suggestions as to who was the scum in your votegroup?<br>
<br>
@Lynx: Not liking you either, so eh. Glad to see you fingering people outside of your votegroup instead of what I was asking.

@Lynx, <a class="postlink post_tag" href="https://forum.mafiascum.net/viewtopic.php?p=6361045#p6361045">678</a>: What. The. Hell.<br>
<br>
@Belisarius, <a class="postlink post_tag" href="https://forum.mafiascum.net/viewtopic.php?p=6361002#p6361002">677</a> &amp; <a class="postlink post_tag" href="https://forum.mafiascum.net/viewtopic.php?p=6361067#p6361067">679</a>: Toshibite, since a vigilante kill is not a lynch. And okay.<br>
<br>
Belisarius, no thoughts on the likelihood in your own group of you, Lynx, dragonspawn, and acryon?

@dragonspawn, <a class="postlink post_tag" href="https://forum.mafiascum.net/viewtopic.php?p=6363601#p6363601">698</a>: This is bad thinking; please amend. Aronis flipped already and is clearly a Roleblocker; no further modifiers were revealed, so it is silly to assert more abilities beyond those noted in the wiki entry for his stated role. Huntress, yes, flipped neighbor. I could conceivably flip neighbor, yes, but would not. You really seem to want a connection between Aronis and I, having decided for some nebulous reason that would concretely make me scum, but your reasoning is beyond me in this case.<br>
<br>
I do not want to give you ammo for your case, but I am going to point out your crazy theory gets less whacko once you drop Aronis and pair up just Huntress and myself as neighbors. Given that advice, I am sure you can have fun drawing up dots there as you please, and I encourage you to do what you feel you must. However, I would also recommend another alley on someone more likely.

Man what a dead-zone, but it will hopefully pick up while I'm gone. <br>
<br>
@Mod: V/LA until Monday morning.

@dragonspawn, <a class="postlink post_tag" href="https://forum.mafiascum.net/viewtopic.php?p=6366199#p6366199">716</a>: Please tell me how that would be instructive.<br>
<br>
Everything else you said seems like so much air to me.<br>
<br>
@Belisarius, <a class="postlink post_tag" href="https://forum.mafiascum.net/viewtopic.php?p=6366122#p6366122">715</a>: bruin's a neighbor?! I got to look and double-check how I missed that, if I did. (Really? Aaagh.)<br>
<br>
@Lynx, <a class="postlink post_tag" href="https://forum.mafiascum.net/viewtopic.php?p=6366003#p6366003">714</a>: Come up with arguments for it! <img class="smilies" src="./images/smilies/icon_neutral.gif" width="15" height="15" alt=":|" title="Neutral">

@SleepyKrew, <a class="postlink post_tag" href="https://forum.mafiascum.net/viewtopic.php?p=6398219#p6398219">813</a>: You are not confirmed town by not hammering Belisarius. Alternate solution: Belisarius may be town but you are the only mafia left. Hammering would have gotten you another town lynch, but would not auto-win you the game. The following Day would be difficult (ideally). It is within the realm of possibility.<br>
<br>
@SleepyKrew, <a class="postlink post_tag" href="https://forum.mafiascum.net/viewtopic.php?p=6398247#p6398247">817</a>: That claim is just ugh. I am not going to challenge it with a vote and it might fly, but it stinks, especially since you magically forgot you had a non-vanilla role.

@Belisarius, <a class="postlink post_tag" href="https://forum.mafiascum.net/viewtopic.php?p=6402787#p6402787">855</a>: acryon could have been banking on that, and bruin could be your buddy. Anything is possible. You could do yourself a favor and save yourself when you know you are town and get rid of one of your reads.<br>
<br>
Seeing as you are my likely suspect or a key to others, I cannot apologize for going where my suspicions lead.

@bruin, <a class="postlink post_tag" href="https://forum.mafiascum.net/viewtopic.php?p=6406330#p6406330">876</a>: That is one hell of a correction.<br>
<br>
@SleepyKrew, <a class="postlink post_tag" href="https://forum.mafiascum.net/viewtopic.php?p=6406571#p6406571">878</a> &amp; <a class="postlink post_tag" href="https://forum.mafiascum.net/viewtopic.php?p=6406586#p6406586">879</a>: This is my third game here; I was approximating by the number of players. I do not know what is usual/unusual.<br>
<br>
If we are going to pretend Madonna knows what is up by theorizing two scum slots initially and by Day 4 be working under a three scum slot assumption (and saying that is fishy), the reason for the change of heart could be because others pushed that idea (<a class="postlink post_tag" href="https://forum.mafiascum.net/viewtopic.php?p=6389485#p6389485">768</a> &amp; <a class="postlink post_tag" href="https://forum.mafiascum.net/viewtopic.php?p=6392034#p6392034">779</a>) and so if that is what I have to work with to work with town, so be it.

@Belisarius, <a class="postlink post_tag" href="https://forum.mafiascum.net/viewtopic.php?p=6404891#p6404891">867</a>: This is meta stuff in 867 to which I do not subscribe because other games' outcomes do not affect this game. Tactics, maybe, but unless you are pointing out a specific play and where this game's players are doing the analogue to said specific play, this is all bullshit, especially concern about who is responsible for losing. I am sure the dead thread has plenty of nominations for who sucks here, but all of this is for the after-party, not today.<br>
<br>
@Belisarius, <a class="postlink post_tag" href="https://forum.mafiascum.net/viewtopic.php?p=6404898#p6404898">868</a>: Later you can claim you are absolved of all guilt since you handed off responsibility for your vote, wow. This, to me, is the equivalent to handing your job to think over to a RNG.
